Exercise 2.1 (2.8 in Gut's book)
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series default
The density function of the two-dimensional random variable 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(X,Y\right)$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{X,Y}\left(x,y\right)=\begin{cases}
\frac{x^{2}}{2\cdot y^{3}}\cdot e^{-\frac{x}{y}} & ,\,0<x<\infty,\,0<y<1\\
0 & ,\,\text{otherwise.}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
(a) Determine the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
(b) Find the conditional distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 given that 
\begin_inset Formula $Y=y$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
(c) Use the results from (a) and (b) to compute 
\begin_inset Formula $E\left(X\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Var\left(X\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

