Exercise 2.2 (2.11 in Gut's book)
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series default
Suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 have a joint density function given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{X,Y}\left(x,y\right)=\begin{cases}
c\cdot x^{2}y & ,\,0<y<x<1\\
0 & ,\,\text{otherwise.}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

Compute 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

, the marginal densities, 
\begin_inset Formula $E\left(X\right)$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $E\left(Y\right)$
\end_inset

, and the conditional expectations 
\begin_inset Formula $E\left(Y|X=x\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $E\left(X|Y=y\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

