Exercise 2.3 (2.33 in Gut's book)
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series default
Suppose that the random variable 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is uniformly distributed symmetrically around zero, but in such a way that
 the parameter is uniform on 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(0,1\right)$
\end_inset

; that is, suppose that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
X|A=a\sim U\left(-a,a\right)\,\,\text{with}\,\, A\sim U\left(0,1\right).
\]

\end_inset

Find the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $E\left(X\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Var\left(X\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

